				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Pook's Useless Banter<a name="26834"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 10 04 9:48 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><b>The Newbie Bard’s Tale</b>
<br />

<br />
Disclaimer:  When I say useless, I mean it.  Don’t expect any greater lightstones here.  My toadstool is big enough for the both of us, though, so feel free to explore the less than deep thoughts of a friendly elf.  I strive for that rush I get when I perform something right.  That doesn’t happen too often, so don’t be alarmed if you think this might be a continuous lament.
<br />

<br />
<b><i>Shutting Up Sideline Mob Casters</i></b>
<br />

<br />
There is nothing like the cozy feeling I get when I perform for some MOB for five minutes, leaving them passed out in exhaustion while I trot along refreshed to the next town.  So, you can imagine the insanity of a new MOB caster pounding on the backstage door.
<br />

<br />
One of a MOB caster’s favorite tricks is to heal his buddy during your performance.  This occurs when you personally are out of the caster’s agro range.  All it sees is one of its buddies with less than sufficient health.  So it decides to stick around and sling heal spells.  The MOB caster parks itself and never really gets close enough to realize that you are trying to do a show here.
<br />

<br />
I guess most would just move the performance to another location, but this Elf got a little offended by the intrusion.  I mean, this is my stage, if you don’t like what I’m playing, bug off.  In order to help them along, these sideline casters are begging for Kelin’s Lugubrious Lament.  
<br />

<br />
What I have to appreciate about this song is that it is a polite way to say “you’re not invited” without ruffling any feathers; so no need to deal with them later.  Try it sometime when you are really into your performance and don’t want to break away later to sign autographs.  Just be sure that you’re bigger than he is, or your new fan just might want to be a part of your act. 
<br />

<br />
Pook
<br />
Stormhammer
<br />
</span></td>
